---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About — Gabriel Rubens">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">// about</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">Gabriel <em>Rubens</em>.</h1>

  <div class="about-grid">
    <div class="prose">
      <p style="font-size:1.2rem;color:var(--ink)">
        I'm a solo builder based in Portugal, originally from Brazil. I spent a
        decade working in teams before deciding to see what I could make on my
        own, on the side of everything else.
      </p>
      <p>
        I build small, humane software. Four products so far, shipped and
        maintained by one person: Pensio, GotHired, Gravity, and HobbyCat. I
        tend to reach for <strong>Rails, Hotwire, and Hotwire Native</strong> —
        tools built for one person to ship a lot. Postgres on the back, Kamal
        to deploy, a VPS to run it.
      </p>
      <p>
        My thesis is plain: the internet has enough aggressive,
        attention-grabbing software. What it's short on is tools that are kind
        — that assume you will skip days, forget things, change your mind. I
        try to make those.
      </p>
      <p>
        If any of that resonates, or you want to say hi, I'm easy to find.
      </p>
    </div>

    <aside class="about-aside">
      <dl>
        <div><dt>based</dt><dd>Portugal</dd></div>
        <div><dt>from</dt><dd>Brazil</dd></div>
        <div>
          <dt>stack</dt>
          <dd class="stack">
            <span>Rails</span><span>Hotwire</span><span>Django</span><span>Postgres</span><span>Kamal</span>
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div><dt>ship count</dt><dd>4 products · all live</dd></div>
        <div>
          <dt>elsewhere</dt>
          <dd>
            <a href="https://twitter.com/gabrielrubens" target="_blank" rel="noopener">twitter</a> ·
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/gabrielrubens" target="_blank" rel="noopener">linkedin</a>
          </dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </aside>
  </div>
</Base>
